<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1212999>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Cyllopsis tomemmeli genitalia: a) male genitalia in left lateral view (appendices angulares indicated as app.ang.); b) aedeagus;c) tip of valvain dorsalview; d) juxta(all drawings basedon genitalic dissection SN-17-68); e)female genitalia in dorsal view; f) female genitalia in ventral view (ductus bursae and corpus bursae omitted, modified scales indicated); g) signa (all drawings and photo based on genitalic dissection SN-14-191). Upper scale bar for male genitalia, bottom scale bar for female genitalia except for (g). Both scale bars indicating 1mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1212999/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1213001>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Pine forest habitat approximately 2 kilometers NW of the type locality of C. tomemmeli, about 12 kilometers SE of San Cristóbal de Las Casas, Chiapas, Mexico, March 26, 1959, photo by Thomas C. Emmel." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1213001/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

